      "Distinguish reversible ischemia from transmural necrosis"
    ],
    "clinical_pearls": [
      "Always include non-contrast phase to see calcification and hemorrhage",
      "Arterial and venous phases are both essential - don't skip venous",
      "Pneumatosis + portal gas = assume necrosis until proven otherwise",
      "Patent main vessels doesn't exclude NOMI - look at branches"
    ]
